{"id":30,"parent_id":0,"book_id":80,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":30,"title":"Chapter 27: Korihor","subtitle":"","short_title":"Chapter 27","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor","content":[["div",{"id":"container","role":"main"},["div",{"type":"chapter","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor"},[".heading",{"id":"head1","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.head1"},[".titleNumber","Chapter 27"],["h1","Korihor"]],[".bodyBlock",[".image",{"id":"f1","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.f1"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_030_01.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p3","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.p3"},"A man named Korihor came to Zarahemla. He did not believe in Jesus Christ and preached that what the prophets had said about the Savior was not true."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p4","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.p4"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/30.6,12-14"},"Alma 30:6, 12–14"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f2","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.f2"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_030_02.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p5","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.p5"},"Korihor told the people they were foolish to believe that Jesus would come to the earth and suffer for their sins."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p6","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.p6"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/30.16"},"Alma 30:16"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f3","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.f3"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_030_03.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p7","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.p7"},"He said people could not be punished for their sins because there was no life after death. Many people believed Korihor. They became wicked."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p8","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.p8"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/30.17-18"},"Alma 30:17–18"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f4","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.f4"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_030_04.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p9","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.p9"},"Korihor tried preaching to the people of Ammon, but they would not listen. They tied him up and took him to Ammon, who forced him out of the city."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p10","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.p10"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/30.19-21"},"Alma 30:19–21"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f5","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.f5"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_030_05.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p11","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.p11"},"Korihor went to the land of Gideon, but the people there would not listen to him either. The chief judge sent him to Alma."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p12","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.p12"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/30.21,29"},"Alma 30:21, 29"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f6","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.f6"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_030_06.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p13","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.p13"},"Alma asked Korihor if he believed in God. Korihor said he did not. Alma testified that there is a God and that Christ would come."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p14","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.p14"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/30.37-39"},"Alma 30:37–39"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f7","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.f7"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_030_07.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p15","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.p15"},"Korihor wanted Alma to perform a miracle to prove there is a God. Korihor said he would believe in God if he saw a sign of God’s power."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p16","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.p16"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/30.43"},"Alma 30:43"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f8","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.f8"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_030_08.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p17","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.p17"},"Alma told Korihor he had already seen many signs of God’s power through the scriptures and the testimonies of all the prophets."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p18","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.p18"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/30.44"},"Alma 30:44"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f9","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.f9"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_030_09.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p19","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.p19"},"Alma said the earth and everything on it and the movement of the planets in the sky are also signs that there is a God."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p20","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.p20"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/30.44"},"Alma 30:44"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f10","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.f10"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_030_10.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p21","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.p21"},"Korihor still refused to believe. Alma was sad because of Korihor’s wickedness and warned him that his soul might be destroyed."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p22","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.p22"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/30.45-46"},"Alma 30:45–46"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f11","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.f11"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_030_11.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p23","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.p23"},"Korihor still wanted a sign to prove there is a God. Alma said the sign from God would be that Korihor would not be able to speak."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p24","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.p24"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/30.48-49"},"Alma 30:48–49"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f12","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.f12"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_030_12.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p25","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.p25"},"After Alma said this, Korihor could not speak."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p26","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.p26"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/30.50"},"Alma 30:50"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f13","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.f13"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_030_13.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p27","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.p27"},"Korihor wrote that he knew this sign was from God and that he had always known there is a God. He asked Alma to pray and remove the curse."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p28","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.p28"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/30.52,54"},"Alma 30:52, 54"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f14","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.f14"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_030_14.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p29","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.p29"},"Alma knew that if Korihor could speak he would lie again to the people. Alma said the Lord would decide if Korihor would speak again."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p30","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.p30"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/30.55"},"Alma 30:55"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f15","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.f15"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_030_15.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p31","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.p31"},"The Lord did not give Korihor back his speech. Korihor went from house to house, begging for food."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p32","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.p32"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/30.56"},"Alma 30:56"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f16","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.f16"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_030_16.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p33","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.p33"},"The chief judge sent a letter throughout the land telling what had happened to Korihor. He told those who had believed Korihor to repent. The people repented."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p34","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.p34"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/30.57-58"},"Alma 30:57–58"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f17","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.f17"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_030_17.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p35","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.p35"},"Korihor went to live with the Zoramites. One day while he was begging, he was trampled to death."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p36","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-27-korihor.p36"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/30.59"},"Alma 30:59"]]]]]]]],"refs":null}
